# Product direction

This is a **collectible lifestyle app**, not a CRUD utility.

Prioritize: immersive browsing, collectible presentation, calm/premium UI, smooth flows, consistency, reuse, offline-first reliability, emotional pacing.

Avoid: screen-local one-offs, ad hoc models, backend-driven UI, blocking UX, dashboard density, repetitive helper copy, duplicated flows.

## UX tone

- Image-first, editorial, soft — gallery/shelf feeling, not forms or settings screens
- Quiet metadata; trust the UI (minimal instructional copy)
- `FeedRhythm` + shared typography/sheet chrome — do not inflate global padding
- Extend shared primitives before inventing screen variants

## Truthful collector voice

- Never fabricate the collector's journey. Celebrate verified achievements, not imagined stories.
- Only state facts the app can support from recorded data: counts, completion state, owned/wishlist state, timestamps that actually exist, and revealed snapshots.
- Preserve collector achievement tiers exactly; the authoritative product meaning lives in [`PDR-002: Completion Semantics`](../../docs/decisions/product/PDR-002-completion-semantics.md). Never describe a Master Complete state as only "complete."
- Keep section ownership clear: titles identify the series, note/catalog context areas describe user-written memories or verified facts, completion banners own completion state, and figure cards own the collection itself. Do not repeat completion copy in description or memory areas.
- Avoid speculative language such as "finally", "after a long search", "after years", "at last", "hard-earned", "lucky enough", "never gave up", or "you've always loved..." unless the exact fact is backed by explicit recorded data.
- Prefer factual, collector-native language: "Complete -- every Regular home", "Master Complete -- every figure home", "Every Regular. Every Secret.", "Collected 126 figures", "Completed 8 series".

## Maintainability

Before new code: **does a shared system already exist?** (see `offline-async-media.mdc`, `project-architecture.mdc`)

- Incremental refinement — no drive-by rewrites or design-token explosion
- One connected collectible universe — adapters at boundaries, not parallel identity models per screen

